# PIXIJS v8 DEVELOPMENT RULES & CORE API

## CRITICAL — DO NOT BREAK (hard errors or undefined behavior)

| # | Rule | Wrong | Right |
|---|------|-------|-------|
| C1 | Application constructor takes NO args. All config goes to `await app.init({...})`. | `new Application({width:800})` | `new Application(); await app.init({width:800})` |
| C2 | Never access `app.canvas`, `app.renderer`, or `app.screen` before `await app.init()` resolves. | `document.body.appendChild(app.canvas); app.init(...)` | `await app.init(...); document.body.appendChild(app.canvas)` |
| C3 | Use `app.canvas`, NOT `app.view` (v7 alias, deprecated). | `app.view` | `app.canvas` |
| C4 | Never add children to leaf objects: Sprite, Graphics, Text, Mesh, ParticleContainer, DOMContainer, GifSprite. Wrap leaves in `Container` if grouping is needed. | `sprite.addChild(graphics)` | `new Container().addChild(sprite, graphics)` |
| C5 | `DisplayObject` does NOT exist in v8. Use `Container` as the base type for all display objects. | `function f(d: DisplayObject)` | `function f(d: Container)` |
| C6 | `Texture.from(url)` does NOT fetch. It reads cache only. Use `await Assets.load(url)` to load, then `Texture.from(...)` or direct return value. | `Texture.from("img.png")` | `await Assets.load("img.png")` |
| C7 | `app.destroy()` without `releaseGlobalResources: true` leaks pooled batches/textures into the next Application instance. | `app.destroy()` | `app.destroy({ releaseGlobalResources: true })` |
| C8 | Ticker callbacks receive the `Ticker` instance, not a delta number. Read `.deltaTime` or `.deltaMS` from it. | `app.ticker.add((dt) => { sprite.x += dt })` | `app.ticker.add((t) => { sprite.x += t.deltaTime })` |

## HIGH — severe performance or correctness issues

| # | Rule | Wrong | Right |
|---|------|-------|-------|
| H1 | Use `eventMode = 'static'` explicitly. Default is `'passive'` (no events). | `sprite.on('pointerdown', ...)` without eventMode | `sprite.eventMode = 'static'; sprite.on(...)` |
| H2 | `buttonMode` removed. Use `cursor = 'pointer'` instead. | `sprite.buttonMode = true` | `sprite.cursor = 'pointer'` |
| H3 | Drag needs `globalpointermove`, not `pointermove`. In v8 move events fire only over the hit object. | `sprite.on('pointermove', drag)` | `sprite.on('globalpointermove', drag)` |
| H4 | `Assets.add(key, url)` signature removed. Use `{ alias, src }` object. | `Assets.add('bunny', 'bunny.png')` | `Assets.add({ alias: 'bunny', src: 'bunny.png' })` |
| H5 | `updateTransform()` removed in v8. Use `onRender` callback for per-object per-frame logic. | `override updateTransform()` | `sprite.onRender = () => { ... }` |
| H6 | Always set `isRenderGroup: true` on large static subtrees (500+ children). | `new Container()` for 5000 sprites | `new Container({ isRenderGroup: true })` |
| H7 | Group same object types in child order to avoid batch breaks. Sprite/Graphic/Sprite = 3 draws. Sprite/Sprite/Graphic = 2 draws. | interleaved types | grouped types |
| H8 | Use spritesheets over individual textures. Single atlas = better batching + less GPU memory. | 50 individual PNGs | 1 spritesheet JSON + atlas |
| H9 | Never update `Text` or `HTMLText` every frame. Re-renders canvas + GPU upload per change. Use `BitmapText` for dynamic content (scores, timers). | `scoreText.text = ...` in ticker | `BitmapText` in ticker, or guard `Text` with `if (val !== prev)` |
| H10 | Complex Graphics (>~100 points) → render to texture with `renderer.generateTexture()`, display as Sprite. | many complex Graphics redrawn each frame | one Sprite from generated texture |
| H11 | Recycle objects via pools (toggle `visible` + reset props) instead of destroy/recreate. | `sprite.destroy(); new Sprite()` | `bullet.visible = true; pool.get(...)` |
| H12 | Unload textures between levels/scenes: `Assets.unloadBundle()` or `Assets.unload("url")`. | accumulate textures forever | unload on scene transition |

## MEDIUM — avoidable inefficiencies and pitfalls

| # | Rule |
|---|------|
| M1 | `deltaTime` is dimensionless (~1.0 at 60fps), NOT milliseconds. Use `deltaMS` for time-based calculations. |
| M2 | Stagger bulk texture destruction across frames (5/frame max) to avoid frame freezes. |
| M3 | Use `renderer.prepare.upload(container)` before displaying large scenes (requires `import 'pixi.js/prepare'`). |
| M4 | Profile before enabling `resolution: 2` and `antialias: true` — both quadruple fill rate on mobile. |
| M5 | `sortableChildren = true` has no effect unless children actually have distinct `zIndex` values. |
| M6 | `cursor` does NOT inherit from parent. Set on each interactive child individually. |
| M7 | `child.x / child.y` are LOCAL to parent. Use `toGlobal({x:0, y:0})` for world-space coordinates. |
| M8 | Remove from parent BEFORE destroying: `parent.removeChild(sprite); sprite.destroy()`. If mid-frame, defer destroy via `app.ticker.addOnce()`. |
| M9 | Set `container.filterArea` to a known Rectangle when using filters to avoid per-frame bounds measurement. |
| M10 | Release filter memory: `container.filters = null` when no longer needed. |
| M11 | Prefer axis-aligned Rectangle masks (scissor rect, cheapest) over Graphics masks (stencil, mid) over Sprite/alpha masks (filter pipeline, expensive). |
| M12 | Set `interactiveChildren = false` on non-interactive containers and `hitArea` on large containers to speed up hit testing. |

